class Solution {
    public int maximumLengthSubstring(String s) {
        int[] count = new int[26];
        int maxLen = 0, left = 0;
        for (int right = 0; right < s.length(); right++) {
            count[s.charAt(right) - 'a']++;
            while (count[s.charAt(right) - 'a'] > 2) {
                count[s.charAt(left) - 'a']--;
                left++;
            }
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes a sliding window approach with a frequency count array to track character occurrences, efficiently maintaining the condition of at most two occurrences per character within the window.
